        },
        {
          "id": "ad-workflow",
          "label": "AD Workflow",
          "icon": "🕸️",
          "title_prefix": "AD-DOMAIN",
          "default_tags": [
            "oscp",
            "ad",
            "pivot"
          ],
          "body_lines": [
            "# AD Domain: <DOMAIN>",
            "",
            "## 🗺️ Domain Architecture",
            "| Role | Hostname | IP Address | OS / Notes |",
            "|------|----------|------------|------------|",
            "| DC   |          |            |            |",
            "| Srv  |          |            |            |",
            "",
            "## 🔑 Identity Tracker (The Pivot Chain)",
            "| User Context | Method Obtained | Type (Pass/Hash/Ticket) | Target Access |",
            "|--------------|-----------------|-------------------------|---------------|",
            "|              |                 |                         |               |",
            "",
            "## 🔍 AD Enumeration Reminders",
            "- [ ] **Anonymous Access:** Null sessions on SMB or LDAP?",
            "- [ ] **Shares:** Can I read SYSVOL/NETLOGON for scripts/configs?",
            "- [ ] **SPNs:** Any service accounts for Kerberoasting?",
            "- [ ] **BloodHound:** Any 'GenericAll' or 'WriteDacl' paths?",
            "",
            "## 🏗️ Lateral Movement Path",
            "### 1. Foothold",
            "```bash",
            "# Initial Shell Command",
            "```",
            "### 2. Pivoting",
            "- **Finding:** (e.g. Creds in LSASS, cleartext in registry)",
            "```bash",
            "# Pivot Command (psexec, evil-winrm, etc)",
            "```",
            "### 3. Domain Escalation",
            "- **Vector:** (e.g. GPO abuse, Delegation)",
            "",
            "## 🚧 AD 'Stuck' Protocol",
            "1. **Double-Check DNS:** Is /etc/hosts correct?",
            "2. **Clock Skew:** Is Kali time synced with DC? (Kerberos requirement).",
            "3. **Protocols:** If WinRM is closed, try SMB, WMI, or RDP.",
            "",
            "## 🏁 Final Objective",
            "- [ ] **proof.txt on DC:** "
          ]
        }
